Only a few more days of being on the Gold Coast before heading to LA. .
Because I travel a LOT I try to do everything I can to keep my body healthy & my immune system strong. Traveling usually causes me to feel run down which means I'm more susceptible to catching a bug - like what happened on the trip I did at the start of the year. 
So what do I do to help my immune system as much as I can?
I eat nutritious anti-inflammatory foods that don't cause a negative reaction. I have a lot of intolerances as you may already know so when I eat the wrong foods for my body I get very bloated and inflamed. It makes me feel lethargic and gives me tummy pains and takes a while to settle down. 
I exercise but also try to listen to my body & don't push myself when I'm feeling exhausted & run down. 
I rest when I need to & really try to get a decent amount of good quality sleep every night.
I take a high quality L-Glutamine powder 2-3 times a day (1tsp per serve) - this is great for repairing the lining of the gut as well as supporting our immune system & muscle repair & growth.
I take supplements including: multi vitamins, evening primrose oil, iron bisglycinate, bacillus coagulans (probiotics), basic B complex, magnesium, calcium, vitamin C, adrenal support & thyroid support, ashwagandga & also herbal immune support.
I have a super green powder 1-2 times a day as well!
✨I posted photos of these on my IG story!👆🏼
.

I also try not to stress! I take time out to relax, to do things I enjoy, fun things that make me smile or laugh -from walking along the beach to dancing around the house!
I've also started doing RED/Infrared light therapy! I have a light panel at home & use it for about 20 mins/day & find it relaxes me but also gives me energy & it helps me sleep! It has so many more health benefits too including helping with a range of skin conditions, digestion, healing, brain function, muscles etc. I use it at night & put my essential oil diffuser on with relaxing oils & breathe deeply while listening to relaxation music. It really calms me!
I believe it's important to find these routines that you can do that make you feel good & relaxes you! ☺

So those are my tips!👍🏼
.

I went about 10 or 11 days without training and I was going crazy from being so inactive (I need it for my mental health haha). I had my wisdom teeth taken out & have a dry socket (ouch) 😩 so I wasn't able to do much. I've been eating really healthy though...fish & steamed soft veggies have been my staples! Luckily I've still maintained my leanness. It just shows that what you eat is really important for not only your health but for maintaining a healthy body fat percentage. 
I have to admit though, I can't wait to get back into training hard again! 😝 I've been a couple of times now, slowly getting back into it! 
I'm off to LA  next week for a really big fitness shoot and want to feel my best for it so I'm just doing the best I can right now. ☺

Things happen that are out of our control but all we can do is the best we can with what we've got at the time. It could always be worse! 
I hope your week is going well so far! ☺
X Em.

My meals & workout program - link in profile! 👆🏼
I fully believe that combining lots of nutritious food and exercise (resistance training and HIIT) is the best way to burn fat and to feel your best. If you're currently unable to exercise it's not the end of the world though, you can still maintain a healthy and lean physique. I haven't trained in 11 days now (due to dental procedures) and I have managed to continue burning fat and feeling "healthy" solely with the food I'm eating. What you put in your body is so important! Fuel your body with various nourishing foods so you can feel your best. When you're able to get active again you'll be able to continue with your fitness/body goals without having to start all over again. 
Just because you can't do anything physical doesn't mean your healthy eating goes out the window too (which is easy to do I know!! Haha!)😝 - Don't set yourself back further than you need to!  Don't worry about what others are doing or where you COULD be if such and such hadn't have happened.. Just do YOUR best with what you've got at the time! 👍🏼😘
.
@emilyskyefitness @emilyskye_fit .
.

Just a little reminder to anyone out there who may be scared of lifting weights. I've been lifting heavy weights for over 7 years now and I love it! I feel strong mentally and physically, happy and healthy and I feel more confident than ever. I really want you all to feel the same! It may seem scary at first but as you get healthier, fitter and stronger you'll start falling in love with this lifestyle and how it makes you feel and you wont want to stop! The best thing I've ever done is decide to give myself what I deserve - health and happiness. There are a lot of things we can't control but there are a lot of things we can. 
I choose to be active and nourish my body with plenty of healthy food (and treats 1-2 times a week) hehe. ☺

Me trying to understand people @got2bno #got2bme #ad

The older I get in this world, I get more and more isolated. Not a good thing ofcourse, I can feel that new people around me are unsure. They really don't know if they hate, or love me. I guess. I guess i'm not the easiest person to read, but I look at myself as a good reader. Before I was so afraid that people around me would not like me. But now I just ignore it. Don't really know why, but I do. I can't even fake a smile anymore. You can see that my whole face is forced. Haha, god. I guess, that sometimes you meet people you want to have with you forever, and sometimes? Sometimes it's just one more single person in this overcrowded world, just like me. What a silly thing to write.

My brother was driving like a madman trying to get us to the coast on time for sunset. We were still a few miles out when we saw it; a thick wall of sea fog covering the entire coastline and leaving no chance for a view. Disappointment creeped in. We continued anyways and I'm certainly glad we did.
Right after we started walking, the fog was beginning to lift. It made room for the setting sun to break through just enough to create this magical scene.
What had started with disappointment had turned into one of my favorite moments of the trip.
Less space, more life.

New Zealand is full of magic. Travelers trek to Cathedral Cove, a magical destination tucked away on the Coromandel Peninsula. To get there, find the trail at the north end of Hahei Beach and walk along the towering cliff top until the hidden Cathedral Cove beckons you from below. The gigantic arched cavern, white-sand beaches, and seclusion will leave you breathless.

Photo: @andy_mann // Two days ago @kai_lenny rewrote the book of possibilities by crossing Alenuihaha Channel, considered one of the most treacherous crossings in the world, from the big island of Hawaii to Maui. By harnessing open ocean swells, Kai floats above the water on his 5'6" hydrofoil surfboard and rides hidden waves for hours at speeds up to 22 miles an hour. He also swooped up ocean trash along the way. Today he shattered the record from Molokai to Oahu. Thanks for the inspiration, Kai. A team of climbers, Mike Libecki and Angie Payne, approach the unclimbed North Face of Poumaka, a remote jungle tower on Ua Pou Island in the Marquesas Islands. The island geology is mind blowing, with 12 volcanic rock towers jetting out of the misty, tropical jungle. Each tower has its own lore and history, and the pinnacles are a sight to be seen. I’ll never forget the view from this plateau. "When another person makes you suffer, it is because he is suffers deeply within himself, and his suffering is spilling over." -Thinh Nhat Hanh . 
The loop of abuse. As sufferings souls it is not only important to have compassion for others suffering but to take responsibility for our own suffering. I'll say it again... TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY FOR OUR OWN SUFFERING. That is the biggest "I'm sorry" you could give to those you hurt (hurt people, hurt people). DO SOMETHING about you're suffering so that you can stop hurting others and yourself. Stop blaming other for the unresolved in you. Stop victimizing. Stop denying. Stop excusing. Stop seeking the addiction/bandaid. TAKE RESPONSIBILITY & seek help instead. Seeking help is the most courageous thing you could/will ever do. End the cycle. TAKE RESPONSIBILITY.

European tour has come to an end... Closing thoughts or opening thoughts (you decide). Like is a collection of chapters to the books we write, this European tour was another chapter in my book of experiences that has brought greater depth into my stories of love, laughter, grief, anger, pain, sadness, lust, desire, happiness, passion... the list of emotions goes on & on. To feel is such a magnificent gift. When explored with curiosity, expressed into art & shared amongst others with curiosity & acceptance it can enrich our lives in the most unexpected ways. Only when vulnerable enough to explore our complexities can we write our stories that will take us into other dimensions & leave the greater essence of us behind for others to dance on with. Traveling throughout Europe guiding my fellow warriors through my movement therapy techniques for the past month has made my novel that much richer. This journey came at a time in my life when I was in my deepest state of grief. I can most honestly say that the love, truth & acceptance that was shared in my classes has made my heart explode with hope & passion! I look forward to continuing to spread the love for seeking further within through movement & breath (just to be clear I teach MOVEMENT THERAPY classes using dance, yoga & all sort movement influences. All my classes are ALL LEVELS & for anyone 18 yrs of age & up. Please come with no expectations & full acceptance that you might discover something new within). If any of the beautiful souls that I've crossed along the way would like to write me, I always check my DM. Any studios who would like to host me around the world & bring me out please email me at yogancetherapy@gmail.com ***YOGANCE.COM will be updated in the next few days with my latest workshops. For now refer to my IG stories or past captions for what's coming up 😊 (NYC, DC, MD. CA. LA, La Jolla, Michigan, Toronto, JAPAN). BIG THANK YOU TO ALL THAT SUPPORT MY PASSION 🙏❤️😘 #movementismedicine #movementartist #movewithlove #beyoutiful #onelove #movefree #movementart #movementmedicine

Sharing space - 
This morning I was at a cafe. The cafe layout: a very long booth bench that wraps around the walls of the space. 10 tables. Plenty of seating. Older man sits down at the table next to me. Pulls out the morning paper to accompany his morning dose of caffeine. Once settled another man approaches in an angry tone & says "this is MY table. See that's MY water", & points to a glass. Older gentlemen says sorry, gets up slowly, shaking as he grabs his cappuccino & paper. Cafe is "full", all tables are taken but still plenty of seating. I offer the man to share "my" table. He kindly accepts. Plenty of space for everyone. •
I do 'sharing space' exercises often in my classes. They without a doubt are everyone least favorite which is why I insist on doing them. Sharing space puts many people in discomfort, especially when it's so close we are forced to physically touch & connect through eye contact. "What you want me to touch a stranger?" We're not strangers. We share humanity in common which energetically connects us. We're all in this together but you can't imagine the sour reaction I often get. If you can't learn to share space gracefully, hopefully you have enough money to buy yourself another planet, cause I don't think 7.5 billion are going anywhere anytime soon 😂. Gotta practice loving each other & our #beYOUtiful differences. #Onelove #movementtherapy

Upon waking up my morning thoughts have gone from "this can't be real, I need to lay here a bit longer" to "another day of battle, get your ass up & let's fight!" The spectrum of deep emotions I feel throughout a 24hr period is absolute insanity & sometimes I feel just that... insane. Gloriously insane, why so? Because I am so damn proud of myself. Proud that I'm refusing to give up & indulge in my grief (even though respecting its importance & place in the healing process). Proud because I am observing myself w/ compassion & calm like I've never quite been able to before. Life will throw us curve balls left & right, it's not about dodging them (in my humble opinion) I prefer to let them hit me straight in the face so I can LEARN more about myself. It's the only way to learn how to catch them balls like a pro next time (no pun intended 😂 #SingleWomanissues ). Running away from feelings & pretending they don't exist will come back to haunt us even harder. If we stuff our feelings away without resolution, acceptance & understanding, instead of one curve ball,  prepare for an army of them to come at you even harder. So yeah, I'm feeling, it ain't always pretty or fun, but I'm CHOOSING to battle through with self love & courage because I believe I'm worth the fight... and so are you. #AFriendlyReminder #movementismedicine #movementtherapy #beyoutiful #onelove #movementtherapy #feelings #acceptance #selflove #mindmovement

Yesterday's class in Paris was my favorite class I've taught. I didn't teach a sequence/flow. The lesson was much more powerful than a fancy pose could ever be. I taught what my personal practice has been about the past 5 months. Those that did the 'yoga' understood it & felt it's power. The class was about LISTENING & CONNECTING (w/ touch, breath, body, soul & a deep quiet awareness). I believe LISTENING & CONNECTING is what's lacking most in our world today especially in big cities. We don't take the time to practice it because most of us are in such a hurry to feed the ego & EXPECTATIONS of what we WANT, that we miss the importance of what IS; the details, the ever present, ever changing NOW. The humility it takes to allow ourselves to REALLY pay attention (without entertaining) is incredibly life changing & demanding. For the most part I find people are quick to not like these teachings. They get flustered, irritated & are quick to judge that they just want to dance & sweat "like me". I DON'T DANCE & SWEAT; that's the superficial appearance of what I do & clearly missing the entire intention of my life's work. My practice is ALL about listening & answering, rooting & rising, awareness & breath, empowering strength tied in w/delicate subtleties, waiting & responding, questioning, constantly toying w/ mind discomfort. I discover these aspects of myself through MANY techniques. The last thing my practice is about is a handstand or sweaty workout (but if you working deep & internal enough you'll sweat just breathing). My teachings/practice are about being TRUE to myself & my students EACH & EVERY MOMENT, not to entertain. That's what I share generously in my work & hope people will pick up on. MOVEMENT medicine, mediation, therapy... mind movement. Be aware not to judge a book by it's cover cause if you do, you'll miss the most important lessons in life, the ones that really matter. #movementtherapy #beyoutiful #movewithoutapology

This is my last week of the European movement therapy tour. Although I still have 3 cities to go (Paris TONIGHT @healthywarriorsparis , London & Brussels) it's slowly coming to an end.I have many thoughts & things I learned on this journey but I'll save all that for the wrap up. I'm finding that with just 1 week left emotions are running rapid through me yet again. My life has seen dramatic change in the past 5 months due to surprising events (hey that's life!). These events brought severe rapid change. When life surprises us we can either choose to dwell in the memories of what was or we can CHOOSE TO ACCEPT & take life by the balls (of which I'm open for the universe to bring me in human form as well #JustSayin 😂). I mourned the loss of a 13 yr relationship for 2 months. Wept like a baby, screamed uncontrollably & felt intense pain. Month 3 I decided to empower myself. YES A BOLD SOLID CHOICE! I went into this tour ready to explore myself on my own, independent, in a way I haven't known for over 20 yrs. First week was rough, not gonna lie but as time passed & I opened up to all the beauty our world has to offer, the beYOUtiful people I've met along the way, the stories they shared. You guys have reminded me how glorious life is in all its twists & turns. Last week in, I know big change looks ahead yet again. Yes I'm scared but I'm also in complete & utter awe of what life may bring me next. So universe, I come at you with an open heart. I'm listening & ready😊 #movewithoutapology #movementtherapy #movementismedicine #movementartist #beyoutiful #onelove

I was told today that I am so fortunate to feel my feelings so profoundly. What a beautiful sentiment. I've always felt that feeling was such a great gift, even if it's hard sometimes. Feelings gives us colors, helps us grow, be grateful, connect on a deeper level with others & ourselves. I've never been one to run away from feelings. I invite them in happily, all of them, the whole damn familia 😂, the good, bad & ugly, it's all a part of me & I refuse to apologize for any of them. Yes, I ask a lot of questions of myself, I think a lot about what I'm feeling, why I'm feeling that way, I dissect & research my emotions & thoughts profoundly. I interest me, because if I don't find my feelings fascinating enough to explore further how will anyone else truly be able to connect with my soul. I search for profound relationships & connections, so I allow myself to be vulnerable in order to invite those deep connections into my life & have greater understanding. Some find me complicated, an over thinker. I don't think I'm an over thinker at all. I'm just aware & vulnerable enough to explore with curiosity & refuse to imprison my heart & soul to make others comfortable. When I pass on I want to know that I dove into every part of my being even if at times scary & not just sat in the comfortable places of my heart. I love to surround myself with others that do the same, that push past fear to know themselves just that much better. And yes... I will use every tool possible to continue to search deeper & if that makes it uncomfortable or difficult for others, then maybe we weren't meant to explore together for now. One love. BEYOUtiful. #movementartist #movementtherapy #movementismedicine #movewithoutapology #liveloud #livefree

I think there are many (hopefully) times in our lives we feel GRATEFUL but there are only a few very special moments when we can access the depth of gratitude so profoundly that we reach a deeper level of understanding of the true essence of this emotion at its core. This morning was that for me. After having an incredible week emotionally of mostly positive feelings, today I woke up sad, the past haunting me. I had a chat with my best friend @cglur . Her friendship is abundantly generous without being overbearing. Patient, compassionate, detailed in its subtle approaches & incredibly truthful & heartfelt in compassion. Today after we spoke I cried. Not tears of sadness but tears of complete & utter gratitude for this human, this friendship, this trust, this selflessness, this reminder of how lucky I am to have a sister that will pick me up when I fall. I cried because I felt grateful to be able to feel grateful even after all that's happened... all the pain. I am grateful on the deepest level I've ever felt in my life, in the hardest moment of my life. #grateful #movementartist #movewithoutapology #movementismedicine #movementtherapy #onelove #truth #friendship #beyoutiful

Can we please just take a moment to appreciate the beauty of food?🍇Ommmmmmmm..k thank you!🙈 There’s not many things I love more than food photography. It’s amazing how a good picture can bring out the emotions of the food and make your thought run between tastes and flavors! Do you guys have any questions regarding Food Photography, what camera I use, where I shoot, what props I have etc.?🌸 Please comment below and I’ll answer then in my Instagram Stories in the next few days! (p.s.- I don’t eat 3 whole garlics just like that- I was really just a food shot 🙈) Happy Tuesday, xx N #foodphotography #nikonswitzerland #cookbook2 #eatbetternotless

Having a blast in VIETNAM!🥒-When you meet people who have so little but so much happiness in their eyes all you wanna do is laugh together with them & share some of that happiness!!🙈 This lady, Mrs. Suu, was the coolest! We took a few shots and sent them to the lady who came to this local market with us; she then printed them out and gave it to the lady at the market. She said that Mrs. Suu never saw a picture of herself and was so happy and now has it with her all the time; between all the amazingly delicious smelling greens & hectic market life. Happy Tuesday everyone, smile if you haven’t yet today!🙉 xx, N 📷-@tanjasimonewuethrich #vietnam #happiness #cookbook2 #eatbetternotlesstravels

VIETNAM!🥒🥑🍏 -Officially THE heaven of herbs, leaves and most amazing food! Gosh I can’t remember the last time I loved the food in a country to a point where I almost faint because it’s so good!🐒 From all kinds of Phos, to fresh Summer Rolls, Rice Noodle dishes, Banh Cuon and all the other Banh’s and whatever everything is called- if I keep eating like this I will have Vietnamese blood running through my veins by like, tomorrow. (I hope my over-excitement made it clear enough that I simply wanted to say that the food here is THE BOMB haha!🙈) Happy new Weeek everyone, xx N #vietnam #hoian #bestfoodever #eatbetternotlesstravels #cookbook2

HELLO VIETNAM!✈️ -from 15 degrees in South-Korea to 35 degrees in Vietnam. Traveling light? Never heard of it sorry haha!🙈 Love my new bag from @loandsons, it’s so big and handy- I’m the one who always wants to take tons of stuff on the plane from laptop to camera and food. Like I usually bring a fruit-shop on the plane haha!🙊 Always bring food on your flight guys- it’s the best to pack out a juicy mango and eat it like no one’s watching while the others get airplane food. If you haven't yet- try it!🐒 Hope you all had a great Weekend, xx N #vietnam #cookbook2 #eatbetternotlesstravels #loandsons #nikonswitzerland

And I absolutely LOVE IT haha!🙈) xx, N #cookbook2 #eatbetternotlesstravels #seoul #southkorea #dumplings #kimchi #vegetables

Bukchon Hanok Village, SEOUL. 🇰🇷-there's nothing I love more than exploring new countries and tasting my way through all the streets!🙈 In love with the Bibimbap (sort of like a Buddha Bowl) here- so so fresh and delicious! And yap- I'm the one who always wants a big extra portion of veggies on top. Like XXL-extra haha!🙉 Happy Weekend fellas, xx N 📷- @tanjasimonewuethrich #cookbook2 #eatbetternotlesstravels #seoul #southkorea #bukchon

Cacao-Hazelnut-Quinoa Porridge w/ homemade salted & roasted Hazelnut-Vanillabutter, fresh Bluberries, Banana & a drizzle of homemade Hazelnut-Milk.🍇 -can you tell I love Hazelnut haha?🙈 Happy Friday everyone, xx N
SEOUL, South-Korea!🇰🇷 -the haunt for Kimchi, Bibimbap, Mandu and Gimbap has started!🙈 Happy Monday, xx N 📷- @tanjasimonewuethrich #cookbook2 #eatbetternotlesstravels #seoul #southkorea #kimchiland

My kind of Easter Eggs this year!🐰🍃 HAPPY EASTER from South-East Asia everyone- enjoy it to the fullest and please eat some chocolate for me as well!🙉 I gotta get back to rice-dishes, spicy peanut-dips & fresh spring rolls! Xx, N #cookbook2 #eatbetternotlesstravels #southeastasia #eggplants
Peanut-Oats w/ Blackberry-Blueberry Coulis, fresh Figs & Blueberries and salted Hazelnut Crunch!🍇 -one of my all-time favs mhhhh!🙈 Happy Hump Day everyone, xx N

Yakeyama, Japan. Rice fields- 7th of April 2017.❄️ -just a 2 hour train ride from Tokyo and we landed in the snow. And yap- the rice fields, still covered in snow, will be ready to harvest in a few months. The farmers gave us some of their rice to try and I've never ever tasted such delicious rice!! HALLELUJA haha!🙈More pics to follow from Japan, xx N #japan #cookbook2 #eatbetternotlesstravels #itoigawa

Cacao-Banana-Date icecold thick Smoothie Bowl w/ fresh Blueberries, fresh Banana & the crunchiest Oat-Cinnamon Granola!🍇 Mhhhhh, if treats are this delicious, sweet and completely guilt- & refined sugar free I can only say: HELL YEEEAH!🙈 Anyone want a spoon? Xx, N

My guys from the Kampong Chhnang Orphanage 😁

Can't really put into words what our trip to #Cambodia was like, but I'm just so grateful to have been a part of it. Thank you @carlibel for allowing me to be by your side (and film ☺️) for this life-changing experience. These past few days have been some of the best we've ever had together. So many smiles. So much genuinity. So much to take away and learn from. You may look up to me because I'm tall but I'd be lying if I didn't say I'm the one who looks up to you. You've changed so many lives for the better. I have more respect for you than this world knows what to do with. And thank you @wah_foundation for your continued dedication in creating a healthier way of life for these kids and their environment. 🙏 Next stop: Indonesia 🇰🇭✈️🇮🇩

#Carbs = 4️⃣ calories per gram " " "
#Fat = 9️⃣ calories per gram " " "

Indicadores de la semana 
#Urano estará llevando las riendas de la semana. 
Urano es el planeta de las sorpresas, ruptura del orden, del sistema y sobre todo romper con lo repetitivo. Urano nos quita la alfombra del piso mientras estamos parados en ella para que caigamos en cuenta de qué hay otras maneras, que el "caos" nos despierta. Usualmente cuando caemos por A,B o C cae el ego y entendemos qué hay un plan más grande para nosotros y que por mantener una fachada de identidad y estructuras que a veces están obsoletas, limitamos nuestro potencial. 
Esto se lee divertido, pero el joker tiene un humor particular en cuanto a "despertarnos" se trata. Urano es el despido de una Cancer que decía que quería otro trabajo y no se atrevía a renunciar. Es el nuevo amor de Sagitario que es una copia cómica del que nunca pudo olvidar para que haga el trabajo y rompa patrones. Es el genio que Libra atrae pero no se permite no se deja enamorar porque está muy "loco". Como ya tienen la idea, entienden más o menos la energía predominante de las próximas semanas. Hay algo en lo que tenemos que caer en cuenta con un relámpago para atrevernos a romper con una estructura limitante y empezar a crear una nueva dinámica a partir del 19 de mayo que es cuando #Urano habla con #Saturno en un trino espectacular. Ese trino no se podrá aprovechar a menos que tomemos las lecciones y uranazos ahora. 
Y estas vienen con cada conexión que #Mercurio tiene con el loquito, así que atenta. Varias veces se te recordará que estas viva y despierta, que tienes el chance de liberarte por voluntad propia y no a la fuerza. Recibirás guía, motivación y tendrás energía para reinventarte de manera espectacular. 
Más información en el artículo "overview de mayo" y el #horóscopo extendido de la semana.

Esta semana #Mercurio arranca directo y en aspectos muy interesantes. 
Varias veces les he mencionado que está en orbe muy cercana a #Urano (a-ha! moments, eureka!, romper patrones) que esta energía se ha mantenido por un rato y se incrementa con el despertar de #Mercurio el 3 de mayo y con la #LunaLlena en Escorpio el 10. 
Entonces será esta semana y la que viene en las que nos veremos ante la elección de actuar diferente y encontrar nuevas soluciones a viejos estímulos y "problemas"

Entiende que... 1.- "Problema" es una palabra código para aprender y hacerlo mejor la próxima vez. Con debida meditación y observación, cada bloqueo es para centrarnos y darle con más fuerza y certeza. 
2.-Que el cambio sucede cuando ante el mismo estímulo, decides actuar diferente. Esto es lo que permite crecimiento y continuidad a la par en nuestras vidas. Cuando no queremos cambiar, usualmente perdemos cosas y personas. Cambiar por voluntad propia pensando en el beneficio de los envueltos nos lleva a la continuidad de situaciones y vínculos a los que le inyectamos luz. 
3.- La inteligencia intelectual y emocional de una persona se mide con la pausa entre un estímulo y la reacción. Si reacciono inmediatamente ante un estímulo, lo más seguro es que lo hago en piloto automático basada en antecedentes y como resultado estaré recreando pasado en mi presente. Por eso situaciones se repiten incesantemente. 
Entonces no culpes a la noche, a la playa, a la lluvia, o a Mercurio. Está haciendo lo más que puede para generar un cambio de patrones pero el trabajo en tu vida lo haces tú. Su retrogradación de 21 días nos ha dado claves sobre cómo pensamos, operamos y nos damos/restamos estabilidad. 
Así que sin excusas. Mercurio retro es siempre un regalo.

Tengo varios días hablándoles sobre lo que está haciendo #Mercurio (noticias, entendimiento, comunicación)  al estar alineándose con #Urano (sorpresa, romper tradiciones, romper con el pasado) y es una influencia que se mantiene hasta el 15 de mayo. 
Esa energía de "no lo había visto así y ahora que lo veo diferente quiero hacer las cosas diferente" se mantiene, y quiero que lo recuerden y que o se confundan con lo que voy a explicar ahora: 
Hoy tenemos una tensión entre dos grandes: #Saturno (limitaciones) y #Quiron (heridas emocionales) 
Esta cuadratura es como la cereza en el tope del helado de las que tuvo #Venus (deseo) vs Saturno y junto a Quiron que empezaron en el 27 de enero, luego el 8 de abril y la última fue el 21 de abril. Esas cuadraturas que incluían a #Venus nos enseñaron que no todo lo que deseamos nos conviene, que teníamos que aprender a mantener el vacío y verlo como espacio para un deseo del alma, para algo mejor. 
Cuando #Venus tenía estás tensiones, la sensación era "quiero, pero no puedo tenerlo" o "quiero pero sé que no es para mi" y ahora que es Saturno y Quiron los que conversan, realmente caemos en cuenta de la limitación que tenemos para alcanzar lo que queremos a menos que trabajemos heridas emocionales del pasado y que soltemos lo que ya se ha hecho evidente que no es para nuestro camino y evolución. 
Y aquí vuelvo con la unión #Mercurio / #Urano...¿cómo pinta en todo esto?  Como la unión sigue activa, verás que vía noticia, información, encuentro o uniendo los puntos caes en cuenta de algo que te saca de tu centro y es lo que hace que caigas en cuenta de que aún falta por sanar. Es como si ya te habías creido superada en cierto tema y algo te despierta y te recuerda que aún hay más trabajo interno que hacer. 
Por eso hoy puede se un día emocional, de melancolía. A esto se suma la Luna en #Cancer (agua = sensibilidad) y el cambio de nodos que también implica soltar algo (vean posts del fin de semana)

Hoy conocí a Stella, la bebe de @lavidaorganica y es hermosa 🌸🌸 Hay milagros ocurriendo todos los días. Siempre hay razones para trabajar por el mañana. 
Recuerda que tú también eres canal de luz y siempre embarazada de posibilidad. Sin saberlo, todas somos madres de alguna manera. Reconocerlo y celebrarlo nos hace falta 💕💕💕💕💕

"El día de los hechos" pudo ser ayer, puede ser hoy o mañana, en el sentido que (voy por partes para que entiendan) 
1.- #Mercurio (como pensamos, lo que entendemos y de ahí cómo nos llevamos a la acción 👉🏻Marte en Géminis además) está este fin de semana muy cerca de #Urano que es energía para romper patrones, tradiciones, lo habitual. 
Esta unión es como para ir en contra de lo que pensábamos, llevarnos a hacer algo que dijimos que no haríamos. 
Pero... 2.- Esta no es la primera vez que pasa. La primera vez fue el 26 de marzo y allí aunque querías cambiar la manera como algo se estaba dando, te frenaste porque a penas estabas empezando a entender cómo funcionaba ese asunto, esa situación; y sabes cuál es porque es algo a lo que le has amado muchas vueltas y te calienta de alguna manera. 
3.-Esta segunda vez, #Mercurio esta retrógrado. El asunto es el mismo, pero no lo ves igual. Por otros factores, tienes ganas de tomar acción inspirada por esta nueva perspectiva de ese viejo asunto. 
PERO... 4.- Esto volverá a suceder. Hay un climax de esta energía el 3 de mayo que #Mercurio arranca directo y el 9 de mayo que vuelve a conversar con #Urano y al lado de la #LunaLlena más intensa del año, la Luna Llena en Escorpio. 
Imagínate si tomas acción ahora y aún te falta entender algo. Imagínate si estás convencida de que tú ves las cosas diferentes pero el otro no. Imagínate si falta que te enteres de algo. 
No hay juzgado o juez que nos saque de situaciones en las que nos metemos por no saber pausarnos, y hay bastantes alertas y ejercicios de consciencia + evaluación de experiencias que nos ayudan a entender y sentir que si es para ser, pues será. 
Alcen las manos las #Piscis de Sol o ascendente que ya están cambiando de idea en un asunto de valoración personal o inversion de dinero. Ni hablar de las Aries que está RE-volucionadas.

Hoy que el Nodo Sur (la zona por donde conectamos con algo que nos es muy natural pero también por donde desechamos lo que ya no necesitamos) sale de #Piscis, estamos soltando algo que tratamos de mantener a flote por los últimos 19 meses. 
Tomemos unos momentos para decir adiós a... #Aries: una etapa de tu vida que más o menos hace un mes te diste cuenta que ya no daba para más, que ya no eras tú. 
#Tauro: equipo de trabajo, cambio con amistades, ambiente que frecuentabas. 
#Géminis: trabajo, soltar una meta que ya no te interesa, desapegarte a "tu profesión" porque vas a atrévete a hacer algo innovador. 
#Cancer: apego a un lugar y a ciertas creencias. En proceso o muy pronto 👉🏻mudanzas, viajes, graduaciones. 
#Leo: adiós a la falta de límites, al miedo a estar sola o no volver a sentir algo que sentiste antes. 
#Virgo: inestabilidad en relaciones. Fueron casi 2 años de cambios muy fuertes en ese tema. 
#Libra: adiós a la búsqueda de perfección o expectativas que tenias de ti, tu trabajo, tu cuerpo. Ahora más inclinada a la inspiración.

#Escorpio: adiós a limitaciones creativas, a conformarte en relaciones románticas. Ahora: relacionarte c/otro tipo de personas, nuevos proyectos creativos, decisiones importantes por hijos. 
#Sagitario: adiós a heridas emocionales de la infancia. Si al menos no hay "adiós" ya no tienes miedo a trabajarlas o esconderlas. 
#Capricornio: adiós a como enmarcabas un pretérito que no era perfecto. Adiós al apego y terquedad en una postura que de alguna manera terminaba atándote a un lugar o a alguien. 
#Acuario: adiós a patrones de baja estima. 
#Piscis: adios a quien pensabas que eras. Mírate ahora y recuerda como te percibías en septiembre del 2015. Un proceso que empezó ahí ahora llega a su final.

Como si fuera un día de pocos eventos... Hoy también cambian los nodos del #karma. Estos son los puntos matemáticos donde suceden los #eclipses y hacen de dos partes de nuestra rueda zodiacal, un axis de cambios durante 19 meses. 
El tema de los #nodos puede ser uno de los más complicados en la astrología (para principiantes... dejen que caigan en los diferentes tipos de cartas y lecturas) pero es sin duda el tema más apasionante, porque donde caen los #eclipses es donde se generan los cambios más grandes, donde nos encontramos con elementos importantes en relación a nuestro propósito y destino, gracias a las lecciones que cada eclipse nos da ( como un látigo)

En los últimos 19 meses los nodos estaban en #Virgo y #Piscis -que de manera general y podemos verlo al observar cambios colectivos- nos enfocaron en temas como: mejor alimentación, buscar trabajar en elfo que nos inspire, inclinación a actividades que mezclaran lo físico y lo espiritual, cambios a nivel de salud, cuidado al cuerpo, cambio de rutinas, aprender a escucharnos, aprender a dar servicio a través del ejemplo. 
Claro que para entender cómo te afectaron esa serie de eclipses, tienes que saber dónde están estos signos en tu rueda zodiacal, pero seguramente experimentaste cambios grandes en estos temas y más del final de febrero hasta acá porque fue la fecha del último eclipse en Piscis. De hecho, hoy que cambian los nodos, seguramente ves que coincide con un momento en el que estás soltando algo que desde febrero estaba decayendo, y debido a otras alineaciones lo has sentido toda la semana y hasta en tus sueños. 
Bueno... ahora nos #nodos estarán en #Leo y #Acuario que es el axis de la creatividad y salirnos de lo tradicional, atrevernos a brillar. Los temas más importantes son: emprendimiento, como expones tu talento, a quien va dirigido, con quien haces tus proyectos, el ambiente para que tus habilidades florezcan, creación, procreación, romance.

De todo esto les cuento en el segundo clima astrológico del día que está en mi página, junto con una lista de artículos para estudiar sus nodos.

Al final del día, después de "los hechos", lo importante es el significado que le das a lo sucedido, cómo interpretas la situación. 
Nos debemos esto de observar cómo nos hablamos internamente, como interpretamos los hechos y hasta las palabras que usamos para explicarnos internamente lo qué pasa más lo que sentimos. 
De hecho, observar el discurso interno nos ayuda a cachar cuando estamos interpretando una situación nueva con un lente-patrón que no nos hace bien. 
A veces tendemos a interpretar una situación con el lente más pesimista o con el más rosa. No es bueno ir de extremos, pero no nos damos cuenta y mucho de esto ya está en piloto automático. 
Ahora que la #Luna esta en #Géminis, que viene de una conjunción a #Marte y responde a #MercurioRetro junto a Urano, tenemos la misma cantidad de energía disponible para hablarnos duro como para romper el patrón y hacerlo completamente diferente; y se que tienes herramientas para hacerlo, ya que todos hemos trabajado consciencia (en intensivo) en los últimos 3 meses. 
Ps: para muchos este ejercicio empieza ya porque los sueños estuvieron llenos de mensajes. 💋

Esto va desde una persona que te presiona (que quizá incluso no sabe o reconoce conscientemente que te ve como una buena contraparte) hasta "la vida" cuando presenta retos. 
Todo lo que te reta está dándote la oportunidad de crecer, de que te superes a ti misma, de que des lo mejor de ti hasta ahora, expandas tu capacidad y puedas cada vez más. 
Con el clima astrológico del momento esto es algo a tomar en cuenta, para que te respetes y te lleves a hacer el trabajo más allá de tus reacciones de siempre en piloto automático. 
Y también porque veo todo lo que ha hecho #Venus desde el inicio de febrero (cuando entró en #Aries por primera vez) y lo difícil que fueron los últimos 3 meses (sobre todo para las mujeres) en cuanto a algo que querían, creyeron que deseaban, pensaban que les haría bien y bueno no; tuvieron que ver la situación desde adentro, desde el pasado, desde la causa del deseo para pararse ahora y entender que no era reto, que no daría satisfacción, pero que fue una buena lección y ahora sí estamos UP para lo que se siente como "the real deal". Para unas pasó en cuanto a cómo se ven a sí mismas. Para otras al descubrirse en "un nuevo papel", para la gran mayoría pasó en relaciones (no sólo de amor), para las más sensibles en cuestión de límites y para otras (más que todo las que están cerca de su retorno de Saturno) afectó su creatividad.

Recuerda eso y date cuenta que ya estás lista para mucho más, y que de nada sirve perseguir lo que no va o no se quiere quedar. Persigue tu bienestar, persigue el deseo de cultivar tu deseo, de darle el mejor ambiente y condiciones. Persigue tu satisfacción, tus metas, pulir tus fortalezas e invertir en fortalecer tus debilidades sin que te endurezcas en el proceso. Porque esto de ir al fondo y volver (date cuenta) que también se disfruta.

Documenting human rights abuses for @witness_change I came across this young man shackled to the floor of Juba Central Prison in South Sudan. His only crime was to have a mental disability. I made a promise to myself that I would do something for the thousands of people like him in countries with insufficient resources to effectively care for people with mental health issues. 
In many countries around the world, the people I spoke to said there was still so much stigma around mental health. I hope you will join me in fighting stigma and creating a better world for people who need mental health support. 
1 in 4 people around the world, experiences a mental disorder or psychosocial disability in their lifetime. 
In some countries, 98% of people with mental illness and intellectually disability receive no treatment

Find out more at 
https://witnesschange.org/condemned/

“She had made me stay in a chicken hut for three years... her friend told me that its because of the way I behave like a girl that I might rape her kids. She has faced discrimination for most of her life, but she hadn't felt real fear until the media started 'outing' LGBTQI+ Ugandans: “Things worsened when my face appeared in newspaper on the front page. I started receiving phone calls threatening me from different corners that they are going to kill me and my land lord threw me out that he doesn’t entertain gay people.”
